= Schleicher and [+ nsdap_leader +]

In a meeting at the Defense Ministry following Schleicher's resignation, one general proposed resorting to force to prevent a Papen cabinet. Schleicher, however, strongly rejected defying the president, with his military training ruling out any such insubordination: “I am a general, Hindenburg is field marshal. I have been taught obedience.”

Nonetheless, Schleicher set up a meeting between his confidants, General Kurt von Hammerstein, and [+ nsdap_leader +], offering the military’s support on behalf of his candidacy for the chancellorship. He also inquired about whether he could stay on as Defense Minister. Keeping his options open, [+ nsdap_leader +] agreed to keep Schleicher as minister and lied about the current state of progress with negotiations.

